1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
WearEdge Pro is an OPEA-aligned manufacturing agent suite. One Gateway and Megaservice power five plant-floor workflows.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Evidence enters the Gateway, the Megaservice selects a route, RAG retrieves source evidence, and guardrails produce a bounded action card.

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:45,000
The route registry exposes maintenance, IQC, changeover, work instruction, and hazard agents through one API.

4
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Maintenance is the hero demo: gearbox evidence becomes a CMMS-ready work-order draft while root cause and restart permission stay blocked.

5
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:20,000
The IQC route turns defect evidence on an aluminum housing into a QMS quality event and blocks unsupported product release.

6
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:35,000
The changeover route checks SKU setup evidence and holds restart until first-piece sign-off is recorded.

7
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:50,000
The work-instruction route answers from released source instructions and blocks unreleased instructions or interlock bypass guidance.

8
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:05,000
The hazard route detects blocked walkways, PPE gaps, or moving-parts exposure and creates an EHS observation without claiming the area is safe.

9
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:20,000
The scorecard verifies latency, contract pass, guardrails, source match, action target correctness, and route isolation for all five routes.
